The paper deals with the synthesis of reactive systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the modeling of distributed environments as a team of players, which is a topic that falls under the category of Game Theory and Decision Science (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper uses Petri nets to model the multi-player games, which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of programs that interact with a distributed environment, which is a topic that falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
